                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW/2–1545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-15T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 15, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. It is not clear from your recent telegrams what action Venezuela
                    contemplates with respect to entering into a state of war or belligerency.
                    However, the Foreign Office should understand that before Escalante can sign the
                    United Nations Declaration we must have a Venezuelan communication to the effect
                    that Venezuela is “at war.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
